column1: 00 Show reference bases in a specific region|select rb_base_value
column2: rb_position:NEWLINE:from reference_base:NEWLINE:where rb_c_id = 6 and rb_position between 1410 and 1430;

column1: 01 Show reference sequence in a specific region|select concat_bases(rb_base_value)
column3: max(rb_position) as end:NEWLINE:from reference_base:NEWLINE:where rb_c_id = 6 and rb_position between 1410 and 1430;

column1: 10 Show sample bases in a specific region|select sb_read_id
column3: rb_position:NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where rb_c_id = 6 and rb_position between 1410 and 1430 order by sb_read_id

column1: 11 Show aligned reads in a specific region|select sb_read_id
column6: rb_position from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id where rb_c_id = 6 and rb_position between 1410 and 1430:NEWLINE:order by rb_position

column1: 20 Compute genotypes in a specific region|select rb_position
column3: genotype(sb_base_value) as my_genotype:NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset = 0 and rb_c_id = 6 and rb_position between 1410 and 1430:NEWLINE:group by rb_position

column1: 21 Get genotype sequence in specific region|select concat_bases(my_genotype):NEWLINE:from:NEWLINE:select rb_position
column3: genotype(sb_base_value) as my_genotype:NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset = 0 and rb_c_id = 6 and rb_position between 1410 and 1430:NEWLINE:group by rb_position

column1: 30 Get positions with high coverage|select rb_c_id
column3: count(sb_insert_offset) as coverage:NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset = 0:NEWLINE:group by rb_c_id

column4: genotype(sb_base_value) as my_genotype:NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset = 0:NEWLINE:group by rb_c_id

column1: 32 Get variant positions with high coverage|select rb_c_id
column5: count(sb_insert_offset) as coverage:NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset = 0:NEWLINE:group by rb_c_id
column7: rb_base_value:NEWLINE:having rb_base_value <> my_genotype and coverage >= 50:NEWLINE:order by rb_c_id

column1: 33 Show statistics about the genotype|select rb_c_id
column6: count(sb_insert_offset) as coverage:NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset = 0:NEWLINE:group by rb_c_id
column8: rb_base_value:NEWLINE:having rb_base_value <> my_genotype and coverage >= 50:NEWLINE:order by rb_c_id

column1: 40 Show positions with insertions per read|select rb_c_id
column4: count(sb_insert_offset):NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset > 0:NEWLINE:group by rb_c_id

column1: 50 Show positions with deletions per read|select rb_c_id
column4: count(sb_insert_offset):NEWLINE:from sample_base join reference_base on sb_rb_id = rb_id:NEWLINE:where sb_insert_offset = 0 and sb_base_value = 'X':NEWLINE:group by rb_c_id
